Yes, the greedy algorithm always yields an optimal solution. It sorts the jobs in increasing order of duration and then sums up their durations. The time spent by a job is the sum of waiting time and execution time, and by scheduling the jobs in increasing order, the waiting time is minimized, which results in a minimum total time spent by all jobs.

