To format single-quoted text in bold and code fragments with three quotes, you can modify the `format` function and update the way code blocks are handled in the message. Here's an updated version of your function:

```javascript
const format = (message) => {
  // Replace single quotes with bold and single backticks with escaped backticks
  const boldText = message.replace(/('[^']*')/g, '**$1**').replace(/(```)/g, '\\`$1\\`');

  // Split the text into fragments by ``` and format code blocks
  const fragments = boldText.split('```');
  let formattedMessage = '';
  for (let i = 0; i < fragments.length; i++) {
    if (i % 2 === 0) {
      // Even index: non-code fragment, add <code> tag with class="hljs language-undefined"
      formattedMessage += `<code class="hljs language-undefined">${fragments[i]}</code>`;
    } else {
      // Odd index: code fragment, keep as is
      formattedMessage += fragments[i];
    }
  }
  return formattedMessage;
};

const ask_gpt = async (message) => {
