          ${user_image}
      </div>
      <div class="content" id="user_${token}">
          <div class="preformatted">${format(message)}</div>
      </div>
  </div>
  `;

  // ... (the rest of your code)
};
```

This code snippet includes a modified `format` function that first wraps single-quoted text in `**` to make it bold, and escapes single backticks inside code blocks (` ````). Then, it splits the message by ``` and formats non-code fragments with the `<code>` tag and `language-undefined` class. This should achieve the desired output for both single-quoted text and code blocks.

